233
00:20:08,208 --> 00:20:10,833
Being trapped in this prison
six days a week isn't a life.

234
00:20:11,583 --> 00:20:14,625
It's a slow, agonizing,
soul-sucking death.

235
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:22,916
[SIGHS]

236
00:20:23,208 --> 00:20:24,458
[PIANO PLAYING FAINTLY]

237
00:20:24,541 --> 00:20:26,125
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

238
00:20:29,583 --> 00:20:31,125
[PIANO PLAYING]

239
00:20:31,208 --> 00:20:32,541
Move over!

240
00:20:32,708 --> 00:20:36,041
Saturday, let's go.
Or you'll be late for your recital.

241
00:20:39,625 --> 00:20:43,500
[PIANO CONTINUES PLAYING]

242
00:20:43,583 --> 00:20:44,625
[DOOR CLOSING]

243
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:56,583
So... you didn't see her leave...

244
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:02,375
and you don't have any idea
where she might be.

245
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,333
Well...

246
00:21:09,250 --> 00:21:12,291
- When did you see her last?
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]

247
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:13,958
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:21:28,875 --> 00:21:30,958
- [FLOORBOARD CLATTERING]
- [BEEPS]

249
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:34,250
[BEEPING]

250
00:21:35,291 --> 00:21:36,958
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

251
00:21:37,041 --> 00:21:38,041
[GUN COCKING]

252
00:21:39,541 --> 00:21:41,166
[MOANS]

253
00:21:41,250 --> 00:21:43,083
[PANTING]

254
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:47,875
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:57,875
I was just skating and I fell! I did!

256
00:22:00,583 --> 00:22:02,916
[CRYING]

257
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,208
- Oh...
- [WHIMPERS]

258
00:22:08,875 --> 00:22:10,833
[WHIMPERING]

259
00:22:11,666 --> 00:22:13,750
Oh, Thursday...

260
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:15,791
[GROANING]

261
00:22:17,666 --> 00:22:19,416
What if the Bureau caught you?

262
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:23,083
One mistake is all it takes
to put all your lives at risk.

263
00:22:23,166 --> 00:22:26,083
I hate Karen Settman!
I wish I had never been born!

264
00:22:26,166 --> 00:22:27,166
Enough!

265
00:22:30,166 --> 00:22:31,500
You want to get taken away?

266
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:34,250
Get frozen for all eternity
in that god-awful machine

267
00:22:34,333 --> 00:22:36,541
and never see me or your sisters again?

268
00:22:41,208 --> 00:22:42,208
Go.

269
00:22:43,250 --> 00:22:44,791
Monday.

270
00:22:47,958 --> 00:22:51,791
I warned you.
Everything you do affects each other.

271
00:22:51,875 --> 00:22:53,416
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

272
00:22:59,083 --> 00:23:02,166
- What's that for?
- Keep still.

273
00:23:03,041 --> 00:23:04,125
[GROANS]

274
00:23:11,541 --> 00:23:13,375
[CLICKING]

275
00:23:17,083 --> 00:23:18,708
What happens to one of you...

276
00:23:20,041 --> 00:23:21,708
happens to you all.

277
00:23:27,083 --> 00:23:28,208
Monday...

278
00:23:33,041 --> 00:23:34,458
I need you to be brave.

279
00:23:35,791 --> 00:23:37,500
Set an example for your sisters.

280
00:23:42,583 --> 00:23:43,916
Will it hurt?

281
00:23:47,958 --> 00:23:48,958
Yes.

282
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,000
Don't move.

283
00:24:06,541 --> 00:24:07,750
[SCREAMS]

284
00:24:20,791 --> 00:24:22,458
[SHOWER RUNNING]

285
00:24:25,541 --> 00:24:27,708
I bet that rat tasted better going down.

286
00:24:29,458 --> 00:24:31,083
- Shut up.
- [SHOWER CURTAINS CLOSING]

287
00:24:32,750 --> 00:24:35,750
You're burning up. You running a fever?

288
00:24:36,708 --> 00:24:37,708
No.

289
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,041
- You sure?
- I'm fine.

290
00:24:44,083 --> 00:24:46,666
[VOMITS, COUGHS]

291
00:24:46,750 --> 00:24:49,416
- Maybe you should switch days.
- I can do Monday.

292
00:24:51,416 --> 00:24:55,208
Success does not come
without sacrifice and struggle.

293
00:24:56,708 --> 00:24:58,583
[SIGHS]
Shut the fuck up.

294
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:02,916
[BUZZING]

295
00:25:37,833 --> 00:25:40,791
[ELEVATOR WHIRRING]

296
00:25:40,875 --> 00:25:41,708
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

297
00:25:41,791 --> 00:25:46,625
"Beneath the tall tree, while night
comes on gently, dark like me."

298
00:25:46,708 --> 00:25:48,083
Langston Hughes again, Eddie.

299
00:25:48,166 --> 00:25:51,333
- You sound like a broken record.
- And a good day to you, too.

300
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:00,921
[AUTOMATED VOICE] <i>The following items</i>
<i>may not be taken through checkpoints</i>

301
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,458
<i>without prior permission:</i>

302
00:26:02,541 --> 00:26:05,958
<i>any sharp objects, flammables,
or chemicals.</i>

303
00:26:06,041 --> 00:26:07,958
<i>For your safety and security...</i>

304
00:26:19,250 --> 00:26:22,333
<i>The following items may not
be taken through checkpoints</i>

305
00:26:22,416 --> 00:26:23,958
<i>without prior permission:</i>

306
00:26:24,041 --> 00:26:27,500
<i>any sharp objects, flammables,
or chemicals.</i>

307
00:26:27,583 --> 00:26:30,500
<i>For your safety and security,
have your bags ready for inspection...</i>

308
00:26:30,583 --> 00:26:32,824
- Someone's in a rush, huh?
<i>- By an enforcement officer.</i>

309
00:26:32,875 --> 00:26:33,875
Big day at work.

310
00:26:35,458 --> 00:26:36,791
These lines are getting worse.

311
00:26:39,083 --> 00:26:41,933
Last week, a woman gave birth right here
because she couldn't get through.

312
00:26:41,958 --> 00:26:44,791
- No kidding.
- Of course, it had to happen on my day.

313
00:26:45,958 --> 00:26:48,500
Mondays are the worst.
I hate checkpoint duty.

314
00:26:49,125 --> 00:26:50,583
Except I get to see you.

315
00:26:53,458 --> 00:26:54,791
[BEEPING]

316
00:26:54,875 --> 00:26:56,916
I'm afraid I have to ask you
a couple of questions.

317
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:59,079
The Bureau's a stickler for protocol.
You understand.

318
00:27:00,166 --> 00:27:02,666
- What's your name?
- Karen Settman.

319
00:27:02,750 --> 00:27:05,666
- Karen, do you have any siblings?
- No.

320
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:08,166
You carrying any contraband?

321
00:27:08,750 --> 00:27:10,000
No.

322
00:27:10,583 --> 00:27:11,583
Are you sure?

323
00:27:12,958 --> 00:27:15,458
- Do I have to body search you?
- [CHUCKLES]

324
00:27:18,333 --> 00:27:19,708
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

325
00:27:20,416 --> 00:27:21,458
You may proceed.

326
00:27:58,041 --> 00:28:00,291
- Karen.
- Jerry.

327
00:28:01,958 --> 00:28:04,166
[ELEVATOR WHIRRING]

328
00:28:04,250 --> 00:28:05,333
[SIGHS]

329
00:28:07,208 --> 00:28:08,208
So...

330
00:28:09,250 --> 00:28:12,791
Today's the big day, huh?
We'll see who gets the promotion.

331
00:28:14,583 --> 00:28:16,958
All these years, I've been trying
to figure out your angle.

332
00:28:18,666 --> 00:28:22,791
I always thought, with a body like that,
you'd fuck your way to the top.

333
00:28:25,083 --> 00:28:27,208
But then it turns out,
you're a frigid bitch.

334
00:28:30,458 --> 00:28:33,125
- Just because I find you repulsive?
- [CHUCKLES]

335
00:28:37,500 --> 00:28:38,875
You're not interested in anyone.

336
00:28:42,083 --> 00:28:46,333
Working here, night after night,
like a fucking robot.

337
00:28:49,291 --> 00:28:51,250
You think you have us all fooled,
don't you?

338
00:28:51,333 --> 00:28:54,625
I have no idea what you're talking about.

339
00:28:55,583 --> 00:28:56,625
Yes, you do.

340
00:28:56,708 --> 00:28:57,833
[ELEVATOR DINGS, DOORS OPEN]

341
00:29:00,916 --> 00:29:01,916
Karen.

342
00:29:04,166 --> 00:29:05,166
I'm onto you.

343
00:29:07,875 --> 00:29:09,708
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

344
00:29:25,291 --> 00:29:28,583
[CLOCK CHIMING]

345
00:29:28,666 --> 00:29:30,500
[CHIMING CONTINUES FAINTLY]

346
00:29:39,125 --> 00:29:40,333
Where the hell is she?

347
00:29:43,458 --> 00:29:46,875
- Did you try her again?
- Yeah. Straight to voicemail.

348
00:29:47,458 --> 00:29:49,583
- Maybe she got held up.
- She would have called.

349
00:29:51,458 --> 00:29:52,458
Ping her bracelet.

350
00:30:01,791 --> 00:30:04,250
- That's weird.
- What?

351
00:30:04,333 --> 00:30:05,666
Her GPS locator is off.

352
00:30:07,416 --> 00:30:09,208
She's not showing up on the grid.

353
00:30:10,666 --> 00:30:15,291
- She can't just vanish.
- Oh, yes, you can... if you want to.

354
00:30:15,375 --> 00:30:17,083
Maybe she was in an accident.

355
00:30:17,166 --> 00:30:20,291
Run a search.
Um, hospitals, police records.

356
00:30:21,916 --> 00:30:24,333
What if Monday's hurt? Or dead?

357
00:30:25,250 --> 00:30:28,666
And the authorities find her
before we do? [GASPS]

358
00:30:29,958 --> 00:30:33,708
Then... Karen Settman no longer exists.

359
00:30:34,750 --> 00:30:36,541
And our lives are over.

360
00:30:36,625 --> 00:30:39,041
Jeez, she's only a few minutes late.

361
00:30:40,833 --> 00:30:43,541
Monday's never been late
for an end of day meeting.

362
00:30:43,625 --> 00:30:45,166
[SIGHS]

363
00:30:49,541 --> 00:30:50,541
Ever.

364
00:31:15,083 --> 00:31:17,208
[DINGS, BUZZES]

365
00:31:18,416 --> 00:31:20,041
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

366
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,041
[SIGHS]

367
00:31:28,125 --> 00:31:32,583
"Eyes bloodshot from excessive drug use
and emotional distress.

368
00:31:34,333 --> 00:31:36,708
<i>Dark circles under the eyes..."</i>

369
00:31:36,791 --> 00:31:38,500
[VOICE FADING OUT]

370
00:32:05,125 --> 00:32:06,250
- Ow!
- Stay still.

371
00:32:11,166 --> 00:32:13,375
Really? Pot brownie?

372
00:32:14,083 --> 00:32:17,625
It's medicinal.
You know it's good for my nerves.

373
00:32:18,708 --> 00:32:19,916
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

374
00:32:21,125 --> 00:32:23,083
I have a bad feeling about this.

375
00:32:23,666 --> 00:32:26,267
Remember what happened last time
two of us were out there at once.

376
00:32:28,333 --> 00:32:29,333
That was bad.

377
00:32:31,708 --> 00:32:35,583
We gotta figure out where Monday is.
You gotta act as if everything is normal.

378
00:32:36,166 --> 00:32:41,166
Easy for you to say. It's not your day.
What if we've been listed?

379
00:32:42,458 --> 00:32:44,916
Listen to me.
If Karen Settman's been listed,

380
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:47,880
the Bureau would've kicked in the door,
and we'd all be processed by now.

381
00:32:48,875 --> 00:32:49,875
Well...

382
00:32:51,291 --> 00:32:53,875
technically speaking,
one of us would get to live.

383
00:32:55,791 --> 00:32:57,041
[SIGHS]

384
00:32:57,125 --> 00:32:59,208
[ELEVATOR WHIRRING]

385
00:33:06,416 --> 00:33:09,041
- Good morning, Miss Settman.
- Good morning, Eddie.

386
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,916
I didn't see you come home yesterday.

387
00:33:14,083 --> 00:33:18,500
[CHUCKLES]
After hours. Let myself in.

388
00:33:22,625 --> 00:33:24,291
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

389
00:33:42,625 --> 00:33:44,268
[AUTOMATED VOICE]
<i>may not be taken through checkpoints</i>

390
00:33:44,291 --> 00:33:46,125
<i>without prior permission:</i>

391
00:33:46,208 --> 00:33:47,750
<i>any sharp objects,</i>

392
00:33:47,833 --> 00:33:49,416
<i>flammables, or chemicals.</i>

393
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:51,291
<i>For your safety and security,</i>

394
00:33:51,375 --> 00:33:54,875
<i>have your bag ready for inspection
by an enforcement officer.</i>

395
00:33:57,125 --> 00:33:58,125
She's through.

396
00:34:16,708 --> 00:34:17,708
[BEEPS]

397
00:34:23,125 --> 00:34:24,833
So, we got our promotion.

398
00:34:24,916 --> 00:34:26,458
Stay focused, Tuesday.

399
00:34:26,541 --> 00:34:30,041
Check the calendar, desktop,
anything that might give us a clue.

400
00:34:32,083 --> 00:34:32,916
[DOOR OPENS]

401
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,958
I've got the brief
for your conference call.

402
00:34:36,041 --> 00:34:38,375
Vicky, when was the last time
you synched my tablet?

403
00:34:38,458 --> 00:34:41,625
9:03 this morning. Why?

404
00:34:42,333 --> 00:34:44,833
Um, I forgot to log out last night.

405
00:34:45,541 --> 00:34:47,375
You left early to celebrate.

406
00:34:47,833 --> 00:34:49,708
[CHUCKLES]
Yes, of course.

407
00:34:50,666 --> 00:34:51,666
Um...

408
00:34:52,583 --> 00:34:55,166
[CHUCKLES]
Where did I go again?

409
00:34:56,208 --> 00:34:59,333
Your favorite bar. Harry's.

410
00:34:59,416 --> 00:35:03,166
[CHUCKLES]
Yes, of course. Harry's. Thanks.

411
00:35:03,250 --> 00:35:04,250
You're welcome.

412
00:35:05,541 --> 00:35:06,541
[DOOR CLOSES]

413
00:35:17,125 --> 00:35:19,916
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

414
00:35:46,833 --> 00:35:48,625
- [SIGHS] Cheers.
- Cheers.

415
00:35:52,833 --> 00:35:53,833
Mm...

416
00:35:54,833 --> 00:35:55,875
[CHUCKLES]

417
00:35:55,958 --> 00:35:58,500
Last night, um...
do you remember what...

418
00:35:58,583 --> 00:35:59,833
what time I left?

419
00:36:00,416 --> 00:36:03,375
You only stayed for one drink.
You barely touched it.

420
00:36:03,458 --> 00:36:05,458
I think that colleague of yours
put you off.

421
00:36:06,250 --> 00:36:07,250
Yeah.

422
00:36:08,125 --> 00:36:10,416
God, yeah. Which one of them?

423
00:36:11,750 --> 00:36:14,125
You know, that douchebag
in the suspenders.

424
00:36:15,125 --> 00:36:18,000
- Jerry, I think?
- Yeah.

425
00:36:20,791 --> 00:36:23,416
Monday and Jerry argued
just before she left the bar.

426
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,625
[SCOFFS]
He's onto us.

427
00:36:27,583 --> 00:36:30,125
- I knew it.
- Fucking dick sold us out.

428
00:36:30,208 --> 00:36:33,666
Then why aren't we listed?
You've got to corner him, Tuesday.

429
00:36:33,750 --> 00:36:37,416
- Find out what he knows.
- Are you nuts?

430
00:36:37,500 --> 00:36:39,958
He could be the last person
who saw Monday.

431
00:36:40,041 --> 00:36:41,041
[SIGHS]

432
00:36:41,125 --> 00:36:43,750
<i>- He's our only lead.</i>
- Yeah, okay.

433
00:36:47,916 --> 00:36:50,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

434
00:36:54,041 --> 00:36:55,041
[WOMAN]
Miss Settman.

435
00:36:57,916 --> 00:36:58,916
Yes?

436
00:36:59,416 --> 00:37:01,291
Step into the van, please.

437
00:37:02,500 --> 00:37:03,500
Is there a problem?

438
00:37:04,833 --> 00:37:06,791
I don't understand. Who are you?

439
00:37:11,250 --> 00:37:13,958
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

440
00:37:16,250 --> 00:37:17,375
Step into the fucking van.

441
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:26,041
[BEEPING]

442
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:32,291
[BEEPING]

443
00:37:32,375 --> 00:37:33,541
Wha...?

444
00:37:33,625 --> 00:37:36,583
That's weird. I lost her.

445
00:37:36,666 --> 00:37:41,333
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

446
00:37:41,416 --> 00:37:44,875
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

447
00:38:02,458 --> 00:38:03,833
There's obviously been a mistake.

448
00:38:04,541 --> 00:38:06,458
Can you please tell me
what I'm doing here?

449
00:38:34,375 --> 00:38:35,375
[WOMAN]
Miss Settman.

450
00:38:39,208 --> 00:38:41,458
What a pleasure to meet you.

451
00:38:56,458 --> 00:38:57,958
Nicolette Cayman.

452
00:39:01,416 --> 00:39:03,500
I know who you are. Uh...

453
00:39:07,833 --> 00:39:10,125
Can you please tell me why I'm here?

454
00:39:13,375 --> 00:39:14,625
You poor child.

455
00:39:17,291 --> 00:39:20,250
I am amazed you made it this far.

456
00:39:22,541 --> 00:39:25,875
This is... This is all a big mistake.

457
00:39:26,458 --> 00:39:28,041
Seven children.

458
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,833
What was your grandfather thinking?

459
00:39:33,625 --> 00:39:36,583
Do you have any idea
how much food and water

460
00:39:36,666 --> 00:39:39,791
was taken out of others' mouths
so you could be here today?

461
00:39:39,875 --> 00:39:44,791
If everyone were as cruel and selfish
as Terrence Settman,

462
00:39:44,875 --> 00:39:46,416
the world would end tomorrow.

463
00:39:51,708 --> 00:39:53,750
I am an only child.

464
00:39:56,458 --> 00:39:58,375
For your sake, I wish that were true.

465
00:40:00,291 --> 00:40:01,411
There are five of them left.

466
00:40:03,750 --> 00:40:05,958
All the rotten eggs in one basket.

467
00:40:08,291 --> 00:40:10,791
- Is there another way?
- Not if you want to keep it quiet.

468
00:40:14,708 --> 00:40:16,083
[MUTTERING]

469
00:40:16,166 --> 00:40:18,125
What are you doing? Um...

470
00:40:18,208 --> 00:40:19,791
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

471
00:40:20,666 --> 00:40:23,833
I-I work in a bank!
I can get you money! Please! Please!

472
00:40:23,916 --> 00:40:25,875
We can make some kind of deal! Please!

473
00:40:27,333 --> 00:40:28,333
Funny.

474
00:40:30,875 --> 00:40:32,583
That's what the last one said.

475
00:40:37,958 --> 00:40:42,958
No, wait! No! No, please, no!
No, no, no, no!

476
00:40:43,041 --> 00:40:44,416
[SCREAMING]

477
00:40:52,083 --> 00:40:53,875
[BEEPING]

478
00:40:53,958 --> 00:40:55,125
[PANTING]

479
00:40:55,208 --> 00:40:57,500
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

480
00:41:18,250 --> 00:41:20,166
I can't believe this is happening.

481
00:41:21,750 --> 00:41:23,333
We can't just sit here.

482
00:41:24,375 --> 00:41:27,416
We gotta help her. We gotta...
We gotta go out there.

483
00:41:30,791 --> 00:41:35,583
We gotta do something!
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

484
00:41:37,625 --> 00:41:40,208
[GASPS]
Thursday...

485
00:41:51,291 --> 00:41:53,625
[BEEPING]

